1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3175 By: Archer
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to nuclear energy; defining terms;
creating the Oklahoma Advanced Nuclear Energy Office;
8 stating purposes of Office; making certain
authorizations for the Office; prohibiting certain
9 gifts; prohibiting requirement that certain project
be in a specific location; authorizing the adoption
10 of certain rules; requiring certain study be
conducted; requiring report be issued by certain
11 date; requiring Governor appoint director; listing
requirements for director; listing duties of
12 director; authorizing the hiring of staff; requiring
submission of certain strategic plan; authorizing the
13 hiring of a nuclear permitting coordinator; requiring
coordinator have familiarity with certain processes;
14 listing duties of coordinator; requiring coordinator
provide certain assistance; requiring certain
15 documentation be kept and available to public upon
request; creating the Oklahoma Advanced Nuclear
16 Development Revolving Fund; stating type of fund;
stating content of fund; listing purpose of fund;
17 providing for expenditures; requiring the
establishment of certain grant program; providing
18 details on granting of funds; requiring applicants
submit certain information; prohibiting applicants
19 from receiving certain grants; requiring certain
notice of proposed grants; disallowing approval of
20 certain grants if disapproved by certain individuals;
authorizing extension of review; requiring certain
21 written agreement; detailing terms of written
agreement; limiting amount of grant rewards;
22 authorizing certain reimbursement grants; listing
